==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: octahedral
<hw>oc`ta*he"dral</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧k`t⟦adot⟧*h⟦emac⟧"dr⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>octahedron</er>.]</ety> <def>Having eight
faces or sides; of, pertaining to, or formed in, octahedrons; <as>as,
<ex>octahedral</ex> cleavage; an <ex>octahedral</ex>
crystal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>octahedral borax</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>borax
obtained from a saturated solution in octahedral crystals, which contain
five molecules of water of crystallization; distinguished from common or
<contr>prismatic borax</contr>.</cd> -- <col><b>Octahedral iron
ore</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>magnetite.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>octahedrite</ent>⟦br⟧
